# Jira MCP Selection — Personal Repo Only

## ⚠️ Hard Rule — No Exceptions

This repository (`wellbe-2`) is a **personal project**. You MUST ALWAYS use the **`user-mcp-jira-personal`** MCP server for all Jira operations.

**NEVER use `user-mcp-jira-work`** in this repository. Not for reads. Not for writes. Not for lookups. Not under any circumstance.

---

## Correct vs. Incorrect

| Action | ✅ CORRECT | ❌ WRONG — DO NOT DO |
|---|---|---|
| Search for issues | `user-mcp-jira-personal` | `user-mcp-jira-work` |
| Create an issue | `user-mcp-jira-personal` | `user-mcp-jira-work` |
| Update an issue | `user-mcp-jira-personal` | `user-mcp-jira-work` |
| Add a comment | `user-mcp-jira-personal` | `user-mcp-jira-work` |
| Fetch a sprint or board | `user-mcp-jira-personal` | `user-mcp-jira-work` |

---

## Why This Matters

Using `user-mcp-jira-work` in this repo would pollute a separate professional Jira workspace with personal project data. This is irreversible and cannot be undone by the agent. The blast radius is high: wrong project, wrong team, wrong context.

---

## Self-Check Before Every Jira Call

Before calling **any** Jira MCP tool, verify:

> "Which server am I about to call?"

If the answer is anything other than `user-mcp-jira-personal`, **stop and correct it.**
